{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Let {\i f}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?({\i A}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i B}).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 We now consider the function which maps an input {\i a}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?{\i A} of {\i f} to its "geometric representation" (its coordinates in the enclosing space {\i A}\u8197?\u215?\u8197?{\i B}, corresponding to a point of the graph {\i \u915?}{\sub {\i f}}). {\i f\u770?}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?({\i A}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?({\i A}\u8197?\u215?\u8197?{\i B})),\u8198?{\i f\u770?}\u8196?=\u8196?(\u8197?{\i a}\u8196?\u8614?\u8196?({\i a},\u8198?{\i f}({\i a}))\u8197?) We notice that {\i f\u770?}({\i A})\u8196?=\u8196?{\i \u915?}{\sub {\i f}}.\par}
