{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A coproduct of the elements of \u8497? is defined as an object {\i C} of \u55349?\u56478? together with a family of morphisms \{{\i i}{\sub {\i A}}\u8196?:\u8196?{\i A}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i C}\}{\sub {\i A}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?\u8497?} such that for any object {\i Z} and family of morphisms \{{\i f}{\sub {\i A}}\u8196?:\u8196?{\i A}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i Z}\}{\sub {\i A}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?\u8497?}, there exists a unique morphism {\i f}\u8196?:\u8196?{\i C}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i Z} such that the following diagram commutes for all {\i A}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?\u8497?:\par}
