{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In {\b Set}, the fibered product (pullback) of ({\i A},\u8198?{\i \u945?}) and ({\i B},\u8198?{\i \u946?}) over {\i C}, is a special subset of the cartesian product {\i A}\u8197?\u215?\u8197?{\i B} that registers some extra information, pertaining to the functions {\i \u945?} and {\i \u946?}. We write this object as {\i P}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i A}\u215?{\sub {\i \u945?},\u8198?{\i C},\u8198?{\i \u946?}}{\i B}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i A}\u215?{\sub {\i C}}{\i B}\u8196?=\u8196?\{({\i a},\u8198?{\i b})\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?{\i A}\u8197?\u215?\u8197?{\i B}\u8197?\u8739?\u8197?{\i \u945?}({\i a})\u8196?=\u8196?{\i \u946?}({\i b})\}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Concretely, this can also be expressed as {\i P}\u8196?=\u8196?\u8899?{\sub {\i c}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?{\i \u945?}({\i A})\u8197?\u8745?\u8197?{\i \u946?}({\i B})}{\i \u945?}{\super \u8197?\u8722?\u8197?1}[\{{\i c}\}]\u8197?\u215?\u8197?{\i \u946?}{\super \u8197?\u8722?\u8197?1}[\{{\i c}\}]. This is the set of all pairs (of inputs) ({\i a},\u8198?{\i b}) such that {\i \u945?}({\i a})\u8196?=\u8196?{\i \u946?}({\i b}). Let us show this is the case with a simple example.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Let {\i A}\u8196?=\u8196?\{1,\u8198?2,\u8198?3\}, {\i B}\u8196?=\u8196?\{{\i w},\u8198?{\i x},\u8198?{\i y},\u8198?{\i z}\}, and {\i C}\u8196?=\u8196?\{{\i l},\u8198?{\i m},\u8198?{\i n},\u8198?{\i p}\}. We define {\i \u945?}\u8196?:\u8196?{\i A}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i C} as \{(1,\u8198?{\i m}),\u8198?(2,\u8198?{\i m}),\u8198?(3,\u8198?{\i n})\}, and {\i \u946?}\u8196?:\u8196?{\i B}\u8196?\u8594?\u8196?{\i C} as \{({\i w},\u8198?{\i l}),\u8198?({\i x},\u8198?{\i m}),\u8198?({\i y},\u8198?{\i n}),\u8198?({\i z},\u8198?{\i n})\}. We have {\i \u945?}({\i A})\u8196?=\u8196?\{{\i m},\u8198?{\i n}\} and {\i \u946?}({\i B})\u8196?=\u8196?\{{\i l},\u8198?{\i m},\u8198?{\i n}\}, therefore {\i \u945?}({\i A})\u8197?\u8745?\u8197?{\i \u946?}({\i B})\u8196?=\u8196?\{{\i m},\u8198?{\i n}\}. The fibered product is then:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 $$\\begin\{array\}\{lll\}
P &=& (\\alpha^\{-1\}[\\\{m\\\}] \\times \\beta^\{-1\}[\\\{m\\\}]) \\; \\cup \\; (\\alpha^\{-1\}[\\\{n\\\}] \\times \\beta^\{-1\}[\\\{n\\\}]) \\\\
  &=& \\\{ \\\{1,2\\\} \\times \\\{x\\\} \\\} \\; \\cup \\; \\\{ \\\{3\\\} \\times \\\{y,z\\\} \\\} \\\\
  &=& \\\{ (1,x), (2,x) \\\} \\; \\cup \\; \\\{ (3,y), (3,z) \\\} \\\\
  &=& \\\{ (1,x), (2,x), (3,y), (3,z) \\\}
\\end\{array\}$$\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A simple way to verify this is to verify that for each pair ({\i a},\u8198?{\i b}) in {\i P}, {\i \u945?}({\i a})\u8196?=\u8196?{\i \u946?}({\i b}), and that no such other pairs are missing.\par}
