{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Find all elements of {\i D}{\sub 2{\i n}} that commute with every other element. (The parity of n plays a role.)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A pair of elements commute iff {\i x}{\i y}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i y}{\i x}. Let {\i a} be our test element. We want {\i a} to have the property \u8704?{\i x}\u8196?\u8712?\u8196?{\i D}{\sub 2{\i n}},\u8198?{\i a}{\i x}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i x}{\i a}. We can write {\i a}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i x}{\super {\i i}}{\i y}{\super {\i j}} for 0\u8196?\u8804?\u8196?{\i i}\u8196?\u8804?\u8196?1, 0\u8196?\u8804?\u8196?{\i j}\u8196?<\u8196?{\i n}. We have that {\i a}{\i x}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i x}{\super {\i i}}{\i y}{\super {\i j}}{\i x}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i x}{\super {\i i}}{\i y}{\super {\i j}\u8197?\u8722?\u8197?1}({\i y}{\i x})\u8196?=\u8196?{\i x}{\super {\i i}}{\i y}{\super {\i j}\u8197?\u8722?\u8197?1}{\i x}{\i y}{\super \u8197?\u8722?\u8197?1}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i x}{\super {\i i}}{\i y}{\super {\i j}\u8197?\u8722?\u8197?2}{\i x}{\i y}{\super \u8197?\u8722?\u8197?2}\u8196?=\u8196?\u8230?\u8196?=\u8196?{\i x}{\super {\i i}\u8197?+\u8197?1}{\i y}{\super \u8197?\u8722?\u8197?{\i j}}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i x}{\i x}{\super {\i i}}{\i y}{\super \u8197?\u8722?\u8197?{\i j}}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i x}{\i a}\u8242?. Therefore, only elements such that {\i a}\u8242?\u8196?=\u8196?{\i x}{\super {\i i}}{\i y}{\super \u8197?\u8722?\u8197?{\i j}}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i x}{\super {\i i}}{\i y}{\super {\i j}}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i a} commute, this is equivalent (by cancelling the eventual {\i x} on both sides and aggregating the {\i y}\u8217's) to {\i y}{\super 2{\i j}}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i e}, which is true iff {\i j}\u8196?=\u8196?0 or 2{\i j}\u8196?=\u8196?{\i n}. Therefore, if {\i n} is odd, only the identity commutes with all elements, and if {\i n} is even, both the identity and the rotation of angle {\i \u960?} commute with all elements.\par}
