{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs24 2.16)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Find the last digit of 1238237{\super 18238456}. (Work in \u8484?/10\u8484?.)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 We note that 7{\super 2}\u8196?=\u8196?49, 7{\super 3}\u8196?=\u8196?343, and 7{\super 4}\u8196?=\u8196?2401, so the order of 7 in (\u8484?/10\u8484?,\u8198?\u8197?\u215?\u8197?){\super *} is 4. Since multiplication is well-defined in \u8484?/10\u8484?, we have:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 $$\\begin\{aligned\}
[1238237^\{18238456\}]_\{10\}
&= [7]_\{10\}^\{18238456\} \\\\
&= [7]_\{10\}^\{4 \\cdot 4559614\} \\\\
&= ([7]_\{10\}^4)^\{4559614\} \\\\
&= [7^4]_\{10\}^\{4559614\} \\\\
&= [1]_\{10\}^\{4559614\} \\\\
&= [1]_\{10\}
\\end\{aligned\}$$\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Thus, the last digit of this large number is 1.\par}
